Notification SB trigger (second function)
	•	Read {agentId, day, summaryType} from the message.
	•	Query counts only for that summaryType:

String pk = day + "#" + agentId;
String prefix = summaryType + "#";            // "unpaid#" or "progress#"
String filter = "PartitionKey eq '" + esc(pk) + "' and " +
                "RowKey ge '" + esc(prefix) + "' and RowKey lt '" + esc(prefix + "~") + "'";


	•	Aggregate to event-key buckets (the part after summaryType# up to the next #).
	•	Render the unpaid digest or the progress digest using the right template.

Why this works
	•	You’ll send two separate daily emails (if there were events of each type) because the send-control row is unique per (day, agentId, summaryType).
	•	Counting stays fast because the query is a single-partition prefix scan and further narrowed by summaryType.
	•	Templates stay clean: one subject/body for “unpaid” digest; another for “progress” digest.

